CMDR-DOS supports using ALT+NUMBER or CTRL+NUMBER to change the current color.  These keyboard inputs corresponds to special PETSCII codes used to indicate colors.<CON:0D>
<CON:0D>
Inside PRINT statements, typing a double-quote (") enters quote-mode.  Instead of changing colors immediately, the BASIC editor will show a symbol corresponding to that color change.<CON:0D>
<CON:0D>
<CON:FF>ALT+1  = <CON:81>Orange  (CHR$(129))<CON:05><CON:0D>
<CON:FF>ALT+2  = <CON:95>Brown   (CHR$(149))<CON:05><CON:0D>
<CON:FF>ALT+3  = <CON:96>Pink    (CHR$(150))<CON:05><CON:0D>
<CON:FF>ALT+4  = <CON:97>Dk.Grey (CHR$(151))<CON:05><CON:0D>
<CON:FF>ALT+5  = <CON:98>Med.Grey(CHR$(152))<CON:05><CON:0D>
<CON:FF>ALT+6  = <CON:99>Lt.Green(CHR$(153))<CON:05><CON:0D>
<CON:FF>ALT+7  = <CON:9A>Lt.Blue (CHR$(154))<CON:05><CON:0D>
<CON:FF>ALT+8  = <CON:9B>Lt.Grey (CHR$(155))<CON:05><CON:0D>
